s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugh_Duffy" title=3D"Hugh Duffy">Hugh Duffy</a> h=
ad a .440 average for the 1894 season.</figcaption></figure>
<p>In modern times, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Season_(spor=
t)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Season (sport)">season</a> batting avera=
ge of .300 or higher is considered to be excellent, and an average higher t=
han .400 is a nearly unachievable goal. The last <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Major_League_Baseball" title=3D"Major League Baseball">Major=
 League Baseball</a> (MLB) player to do so, with enough <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plate_appearance" title=3D"Plate appearance">plate ap=
pearances</a> to qualify for the batting championship, was <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ted_Williams" title=3D"Ted Williams">Ted Williams<=
/a> of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boston_Red_Sox" title=
=3D"Boston Red Sox">Boston Red Sox</a>, who hit .406 in 1941.<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-SeasonLeaders_4-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-SeasonLeaders-4"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">See also: <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Major_League_Baseball_battin=
g_champions" title=3D"List of Major League Baseball batting champions">List=
 of Major League Baseball batting champions</a></div>
<p>Note that batting averages are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Rounding" title=3D"Rounding">rounded</a>;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball=
)#cite_note-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup> entering the final day of the 1941 season, Willia=
ms was at 179-for-448, which is .39955 and would have been recorded as .400=
 via rounding.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NowlinTed_6-0" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-Now=
linTed-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup> However, Williams played in both games of a <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doubleheader_(baseball)" title=3D"Doublehead=
er (baseball)">doubleheader</a>, went 6-for-8, and ended the season 185-for=
-456,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> which is .=
40570 and becomes .406 when rounded.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-NowlinTed_6-1" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(b=
aseball)#cite_note-NowlinTed-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Since 1941, no <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Lea=
gue" title=3D"American League">American League</a> or <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_League_(baseball)" title=3D"National League (b=
aseball)">National League</a> player has hit .400 or above=E2=80=94the high=
est single-season average in those leagues has been .394 by <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tony_Gwynn" title=3D"Tony Gwynn">Tony Gwynn</a> o=
f the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Diego_Padres" title=3D"S=
an Diego Padres">San Diego Padres</a> in 1994.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-SeasonLea=
ders_4-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batt=
ing_average_(baseball)#cite_note-SeasonLeaders-4"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wade_Boggs" title=3D"Wade Boggs">Wade Boggs</a> =
hit .401 over a 162-game span with Boston from June 9, 1985, to June 6, 198=
6,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-8"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> but never hit=
 above .368 for an MLB season.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-9" class=3D"reference"><a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note=
-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup> There have been numerous attempts to explain the disappearan=
ce of the .400 hitter, with one of the more rigorous discussions of this qu=
estion appearing in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Jay_Go=
uld" title=3D"Stephen Jay Gould">Stephen Jay Gould</a>'s 1996 book <i><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Full_House:_The_Spread_of_Excellence_fr=
om_Plato_to_Darwin" title=3D"Full House: The Spread of Excellence from Plat=
o to Darwin">Full House</a></i>. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/J=
osh_Gibson" title=3D"Josh Gibson">Josh Gibson</a> hit .466 in 1943 while pl=
aying for the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homestead_Grays" tit=
le=3D"Homestead Grays">Homestead Grays</a> of the <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Negro_National_League_(1933%E2%80%931948)" title=3D"Negro N=
ational League (1933=E2=80=931948)">Negro National League</a>, one of sever=
al leagues within <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negro_league_bas=
eball" title=3D"Negro league baseball">Negro league baseball</a> that are n=
ow recognized by MLB.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-JGStats_10-0" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_no=
te-JGStats-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Gibson holds the record for highest major-league career batting aver=
age at .371, four points higher than <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Ty_Cobb" title=3D"Ty Cobb">Ty Cobb</a>, who has the second-highest caree=
r average at .367.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-11"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-12"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>a<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The reco=
rd for lowest career batting average for a player with more than 2,500 at-b=
ats belongs to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Bergen" title=
=3D"Bill Bergen">Bill Bergen</a>, a catcher who played from 1901 to 1911 an=
d recorded a .170 average in 3,028 career at-bats.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average=
_(baseball)#cite_note-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hugh_Duffy" title=3D"Hugh D=
uffy">Hugh Duffy</a>, who played from 1888 to 1906, is credited with the hi=
ghest single-season batting average, having hit .440 in 1894.<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-BAsingleseason_14-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-BAsingleseason-14"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup> The modern-era (post-1900) record for highest batting average for a s=
eason is held by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nap_Lajoie" title=
=3D"Nap Lajoie">Nap Lajoie</a>, who hit .426 in 1901,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-BA=
singleseason_14-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-BAsingleseason-14"><span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> th=
e first year of play for the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ameri=
can_League" title=3D"American League">American League</a>. The modern-era r=
ecord for the lowest batting average for a player that qualified for the ba=
tting title is held by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chris_Davis=
_(baseball)" title=3D"Chris Davis (baseball)">Chris Davis</a>, who hit .168=
 in 2018.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Whi=
le finishing six plate appearances short of qualifying for the batting titl=
e, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adam_Dunn" title=3D"Adam Dunn">=
Adam Dunn</a> of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chicago_White=
_Sox" title=3D"Chicago White Sox">Chicago White Sox</a> hit .159 for the 20=
11 season, nine points lower than the record.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(ba=
seball)#cite_note-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The highest batting average for a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rookie" title=3D"Rookie">rookie</a> was .=
408 in 1911 by <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shoeless_Joe_Jackso=
n" title=3D"Shoeless Joe Jackson">Shoeless Joe Jackson</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-BArecords_17-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-BArecords-17"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The league batting average in MLB for the <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/2018_Major_League_Baseball_season" title=3D"2018 Major Leagu=
e Baseball season">2018 season</a> was .248, with the highest modern-era ML=
B average being .296 in 1930, and the lowest being .237 in 1968.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B=
atting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> For non-pitchers, a bat=
ting average below .230 is often considered poor, and one below .200 is usu=
ally unacceptable. This latter level is sometimes referred to as "The <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mendoza_Line" title=3D"Mendoza Line">Me=
ndoza Line</a>", named for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mario_M=
endoza" title=3D"Mario Mendoza">Mario Mendoza</a>=E2=80=94a lifetime .215 h=
itter but a good defensive shortstop.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#c=
ite_note-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabermetrics" title=3D"Sabe=
rmetrics">Sabermetrics</a>, the study of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Baseball_statistics" title=3D"Baseball statistics">baseball statisti=
cs</a>, considers batting average a weak measure of performance because it =
does not correlate as well as other measures to runs scored, thereby causin=
g it to have little predictive value. Batting average does not take into ac=
count <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base_on_balls" title=3D"Base=
 on balls">bases on balls</a> (walks) or power, whereas other statistics su=
ch as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/On-base_percentage" title=3D=
"On-base percentage">on-base percentage</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Slugging_percentage" title=3D"Slugging percentage">slugging p=
ercentage</a> have been specifically designed to measure such concepts. Add=
ing these statistics together form a player's <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/On-base_plus_slugging" title=3D"On-base plus slugging">on-base =
plus slugging</a> or "OPS". This is commonly seen as a much better, though =
not perfect, indicator of a player's overall batting ability as it is a mea=
sure of hitting for average, hitting for power, and drawing walks.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Anomalies">Anomalies</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DBatting_average_(b=
