ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
w/index.php?title=3DBatting_average_(baseball)&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;sectio=
n=3D9" title=3D"Edit section: Nippon Professional Baseball"><span>edit</spa=
n></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nippon_Professional_Baseball=
" title=3D"Nippon Professional Baseball">Nippon Professional Baseball</a> (=
NPB), the leader in career batting average is <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Isao_Harimoto" title=3D"Isao Harimoto">Isao Harimoto</a>, a mem=
ber of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japanese_Baseball_Hall_=
of_Fame" title=3D"Japanese Baseball Hall of Fame">Japanese Baseball Hall of=
 Fame</a>, who hit .319 in his NPB career.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-42" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batting_average_(baseba=
ll)#cite_note-42"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>41<span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ichi=
ro_Suzuki" title=3D"Ichiro Suzuki">Ichiro Suzuki</a> batted .353 in NPB,<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-43" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Batting_average_(baseball)#cite_note-43"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>42<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> but does not ha=
ve enough NPB career at-bats to qualify for the league's title. <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sadaharu_Oh" title=3D"Sadaharu Oh">Sadaharu O=
h</a> had a batting average of .355 in 1973 season. <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Randy_Bass" title=3D"Randy Bass">Randy Bass</a> had a bat=
ting average of .389 in 1986 season.
</p>
